===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a man {{zh-l|*大}} then drawn as a woman ({{zh-l|*女}}) with two hands pointing to his/her midsection. On top of the character there was huge eye 目, then stylized as a horn 角. The hands gradually shifted upwards; hence, a nearly original version of the character is [[𡢗]]. All the upper part was eventually stylized as {{zh-l|*覀}}. Unrelated to [[栗]] but partly related to [[票]].

Original meaning was “waist” (now {{och-l|腰}}).

